Deep Learning Syllabus

**1. Introduction to Deep Learning**

* History and evolution of Deep Learning
* Difference between Machine Learning and Deep Learning
* Applications of Deep Learning

**2. Neural Networks Basics**

* Biological vs Artificial Neurons
* Perceptron model
* Activation functions (Sigmoid, Tanh, ReLU, Leaky ReLU, Softmax)
* Gradient Descent and Backpropagation

**3. Deep Neural Networks (DNNs)**

* Multilayer Perceptrons (MLPs)
* Training deep networks
* Vanishing and Exploding Gradient problems
* Weight Initialization techniques
* Batch Normalization
* Regularization methods (Dropout, L1/L2 regularization, Early stopping)

**4. Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs)**

* Convolution operation
* Pooling (Max Pooling, Average Pooling)
* CNN Architectures (LeNet, AlexNet, VGG, ResNet, Inception, EfficientNet)
* Transfer Learning using CNNs
* Applications in Image Processing and Computer Vision

**5. Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs)**

* Sequence data and time series
* RNN architecture
* Vanishing Gradient in RNNs
* LSTMs (Long Short-Term Memory)
* GRUs (Gated Recurrent Units)
* Applications in NLP and Speech Processing

**6. Natural Language Processing with Deep Learning**

* Word Embeddings (Word2Vec, GloVe, FastText)
* Sequence-to-Sequence models
* Attention Mechanism
* Transformer architecture
* BERT, GPT, and other modern NLP models

**7. Generative Models**

* Autoencoders
* Variational Autoencoders (VAEs)
* Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs)
* Applications of Generative Models

**8. Advanced Topics in Deep Learning**

* Reinforcement Learning basics
* Deep Q-Networks (DQN)
* Policy Gradient methods
* Meta-Learning
* Few-Shot and Zero-Shot Learning
* Self-Supervised Learning

**9. Optimization Techniques**

* SGD, Momentum, Nesterov Accelerated Gradient
* Adaptive methods: AdaGrad, RMSProp, Adam, AdamW
* Learning Rate Scheduling
* Hyperparameter tuning (Grid Search, Random Search, Bayesian Optimization)

**10. Deployment and Production**

* Model Serving (Flask, FastAPI, Django)
* TensorFlow Serving, TorchServe
* ONNX for model interoperability
* Model Optimization (Quantization, Pruning, Distillation)
* MLOps practices for Deep Learning

**11. Tools and Frameworks**

* TensorFlow
* Keras
* PyTorch
* Hugging Face Transformers
* OpenCV for DL applications

